This paper deals with image classification and segmentation using a novel approach called the fractional wavelet scattering network. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also involves machine learning techniques for feature extraction and classification, which suggests that it could also belong to categories such as machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves image processing and analysis, which could place it in the information retrieval (cs.IR) category.
